sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Frontend Client
    participant Nginx as Nginx (Reverse Proxy)
    participant Auth as Spring Security Filter
    participant JWT as JWT Provider
    participant API as Backend Controllers
    participant S3 as AWS S3

    %% Authentication Flow
    Client->>Nginx: POST /api/auth/login (credentials)
    Nginx->>Auth: Forward Request
    Auth->>API: Authenticate User
    API->>JWT: Generate Token
    JWT-->>API: Signed JWT (HS256)
    API-->>Client: Return JWT Token

    %% Authorization Flow
    Client->>Nginx: GET /api/resumes
    Note right of Client: Authorization: Bearer <token>
    Nginx->>Auth: Forward Request
    Auth->>JWT: Validate Signature & Expiration
    alt Invalid Token
        JWT-->>Auth: Validation Failed
        Auth-->>Client: 401 Unauthorized
    else Valid Token
        JWT-->>Auth: User Claims (Role/ID)
        Auth->>API: Process Request
        API->>API: Verify Resource Ownership (UserId check)
        API-->>Client: 200 OK + Data
    end

    %% Secure S3 Access
    Client->>Nginx: POST /api/resumes/upload
    Nginx->>Auth: Forward + Validate JWT
    Auth->>API: Authorized Upload Request
    API->>S3: PutObject (Using IAM Roles / Access Keys)
    Note right of API: Private Bucket Policy
    S3-->>API: S3 Object URI
    API-->>Client: 201 Created
